headline.main: INDIA PROTESTS STAND VOICED BY CHURCHILL; Council of State Records 'Deep Discontent' by 10-to-6 Vote

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 18 -- India's discontent over Prime Minister Churchill's statement that the Atlantic Charter did not apply to her was recorded today by the Indian Council of State in New Delhi, according to a Reuters message received in London.
abstract: India State Council voices discontent with Churchill interpretation of charter
